        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(secrets): generate secretref reference docs from the credential matrix",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #85969 (replaces the original PR). Adds a shared SecretRef credential-surface Markdown formatter, extends the matrix generator with write/check modes for JSON plus Markdown marker blocks, wires package/preflight scripts, updates generated reference docs, and adds formatter/drift tests.\n\n## Changes from original PR\n\n- **Removed CHANGELOG.md change** — release-owned file\n- **Cross-platform scripts** — wrapped `check:secretref-docs` and `gen:secretref-docs` with `node scripts/run-with-env.mjs` instead of POSIX env assignment\n- **Rebased onto latest main** — clean cherry-pick\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: SecretRef credential matrix and credential-surface docs regenerate cleanly on macOS without POSIX env syntax.\n\n**Real environment tested**: macOS 26.6 (Darwin arm64), Node v22.22.0, OpenClaw source checkout at `8c6e99e82`\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\n# Generate JSON matrix + Markdown docs\npnpm gen:secretref-docs\n\n# Verify docs are in sync (--check mode)\npnpm check:secretref-docs\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\n`gen:secretref-docs` produces a 677-line JSON matrix with 92 credential entries and a 161-line Markdown credential-surface doc:\n\n```\nWrote docs/reference/secretref-user-supplied-credentials-matrix.json\ndocs/reference/secretref-credential-surface.md already in sync\n```\n\n`check:secretref-docs --check` confirms no drift:\n\n```\nsecretref reference docs are in sync.\n```\n\nMatrix integrity — 92 entries across providers/channels/plugins:\n\n| File | Lines | Contents |\n|---|---|---|\n| `secretref-user-supplied-credentials-matrix.json` | 677 | 92 entries covering `agents.*`, `models.providers.*`, `channels.*`, `plugins.*` |\n| `secretref-credential-surface.md` | 161 | Marker-block formatted credential surface reference |\n\nTest suite all pass:\n\n```\n✓ matrix JSON matches generator output\n✓ credential-surface marker blocks match generator output\n✓ matrix and credential-surface marker blocks describe the same registry shape\n\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n     Tests  13 passed (13)\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: Both generation and verification work cross-platform (tested on macOS). No POSIX env assignment required.\n\n**What was not tested**: Windows and Linux behavior (CI covers these).\n\n@clawsweeper re-review\n",
        "branch": "fix/secretref-docs-generate-markdown-v2",
